text:
:flag-et:  *3 days ago* I started *sneezing* and I was *coughing* here and then. By the second day, I was having a hard time *swallowing* anything! *My throat hurts!* 

It was *so hard not to panic,* My monkey mind was stronger than ever!

The 3rd day I used some *_arena_ /አረግሬሳ/* and it looks like I was just panicking from a regular *Pneumonia (ምች)* + a regular *Flu.* Which I have recovered right now *thank God.*

*I believe there are cases like mine which leads to Panicking! Unnecessary phone calls to emergency medical services! Or easily consume false info!* 

So why not build an *online test* that reduces unnecessary emergency traffics and panics? With all current projects going on am confident enough to say we can develop & launch *the simplest Online test* with algorithms that either shows a result _*"You should see a doctor"*_ or _*"Your symptoms are regular"*_ 

_*with methods to cure the problem or further actions suggested if they aren't cured.*_ 
  (Then this data with geolocation in Ethiopia will help us to analyze which areas are highly showing the Covid 19 - *Real symptoms if they ever occur)*  

I build websites for a living *(Am In Gondar, Ethiopia)* but I feel like being a lot better with *UI/UX designing,* So if you believe this could help out *on the side with ongoing projects,* reply and let's do this within *2-3 days!* am willing to put in *every hr on this!*  

Surely we will need *ad campaigns* for people to *run the tests*, People with *Adobe suit, Ui Ux designers* and with *Copywriters* may be *videographers too* for higher quality content, this should be making a huge impact.
Mainly satisfying the term _*"Speed over Perfection"  (I know that there are self-test sites that are helping a lot)*_ 
_What do you think?_

_On top of all Egziabher Yeker Yebeln! Yemarn._

_<@U0107JERE9L>_ _<@UV8B0679P>_ _<@U0106M26108>_

text:
<@UV81AMFSP> Here is NFDA & CDC guideline, MOH can review these docs & modify them as needed. 
National Funeral Director Association|NFDA|
On March 11, At the request of NFDA and as a follow up to the postmortem guidance released by the CDC in late-February, the agency released specific information about funeral and visitation services to help funeral directors safely care for people who have died of confirmed or suspected COVID-19.

While it is possible to have a funeral, they must, in the interim, be limited. Updated guidance released by the White House on March 16 suggests no public gatherings larger than 10 people for the next 15 days. Updated guidance from the CDC released on March 16 suggests no gatherings of more than 50 people for the next eight weeks. Information below offers suggestions for how you may handle services in the interim.
Bodies can be transferred and embalmed using proper PPE.
Decedents can be buried or cremated but state and local requirements may vary.
<https://www.nfda.org/covid-19|https://www.nfda.org/covid-19>

CDC guideline: COVID-19 and Funerals

<https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/faq.html#anchor_1584390222777|https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/faq.html#anchor_1584390222777>

text:
Hi Everyone,
I really appreciate all the effort by everyone on that is volunteering to combat this deadly virus.
The disease spread could be slowed down by implementing disciplined social distancing as per multiple reports around the World. Our society has a tight bond and deep culture of that would make it hard for to effectively apply the social distancing technique.

I would suggest that we reach out to the society constantly reminding everyone this effective technique; and there is no better way in doing this other than the Mobile devices at the hands of 66.2 Million Ethiopians [Source: <https://allafrica.com/stories/201805220680.html>]. Unfortunately there is low number of internet users in Ethiopia; thus we need to also make use of the Cellular Network capabilities.
Thus I believe if we notify the Mobile device holders based on their locations and Population density around them. The individual would be aware of their surroundings.
1.      *Approach using the Cell Tower Triangulation*
See the Following Document for the Graphical description.                                                           <https://docs.google.com/document/d/1TE9XIGdohNtAMdk-AWgdTUSLor6N9qbj4r8HdzugTxA/edit?usp=sharing>

attachments.text: The number of Ethio telecom's customers has reached 66.2 million during the third quarter of the current fiscal year showing a 17pc growth, according to the Ethio telecom.
